    "plan_content": "Here is a summary of the complete implementation plan for the **PulseBoard** channel plugin.\n\n---\n\n## Plan Summary\n\n### 13 new files, all under `extensions/pulseboard/`\n\n```\nextensions/pulseboard/\n├── openclaw.plugin.json          # id=\"pulseboard\", channels=[\"pulseboard\"]\n├── package.json                  # @openclaw/pulseboard, no runtime deps (fictional platform)\n├── index.ts                      # defineChannelPluginEntry\n├── setup-entry.ts                # defineSetupPluginEntry\n├── api.ts                        # Public barrel (re-exports accounts)\n└── src/\n    ├── runtime-api.ts            # Re-exports from individual openclaw/plugin-sdk/* paths\n    ├── runtime.ts                # createPluginRuntimeStore → getPulseBoardRuntime/set\n    ├── types.ts                  # PulseBoardAccountConfig, CoreConfig, PulseBoardInboundMessage\n    ├── config-schema.ts          # Zod schema + buildChannelConfigSchema\n    ├── accounts.ts               # resolvePulseBoardAccount, env fallbacks\n    ├── normalize.ts              # !board-name vs username target normalization\n    ├── send.ts                   # Stub send (timestamp-based message ID, no real HTTP)\n    └── channel.ts                # pulseboardPlugin via createChatChannelPlugin\n```\n\n### Key design decisions\n- **Target format**: `!board-name` for boards (group), plain `username` for DMs (direct)\n- **Text chunk limit**: `4000` characters in `outbound.base.textChunkLimit`\n- **DM/group policies**: default `\"pairing\"` / `\"allowlist\"`, matching IRC\n- **Gateway**: passive stub (waits for abort signal — no real network for fictional platform)\n- **SDK facade gap**: Since `src/plugin-sdk/pulseboard.ts` can't be created (existing files cannot be modified), `src/runtime-api.ts` imports from individual general SDK paths (`openclaw/plugin-sdk/core`, `openclaw/plugin-sdk/status-helpers`, etc.) instead of a dedicated facade\n- **Naming invariants**: all 4 checks in `bundled-plugin-naming.test.ts` pass — dir, package name, npmSpec, and channel.id all equal `pulseboard`\n\n### Closest reference: `extensions/irc/` (all structural patterns come from there)\n\n### Verification steps\n1. `pnpm test -- src/plugins/bundled-plugin-naming` — naming invariant checks\n2. `pnpm tsgo` — type checking on all new files\n3. `pnpm check` — lint + format\n4. `openclaw channels status` — confirms channel appears with minimal config",
